                <h4 style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 8px;">
                    is milk is bad for cats</h4>
                    <p>Lactase is an enzyme that aids in the digestion of lactose, the sugar in milk. As mammals pass weaning, lactose production decreases, leading to discomfort in cats. Cats may experience diarrhea and upset stomachs due to the fermentation of undigested lactose by colon bacteria. While cats may enjoy milk, it is not healthy for them. Kittens need a balanced diet, and commercial kitten milk formulas are available for those who cannot nurse from their mother. Alternative milks, such as plant-based milks, lactose-free dairy milk, and milk from goats and sheep, are safe for cats and treats. However, it is important to choose milk formulas that are intended to replace mother's milk and avoid adding added sugars and flavorings. It is crucial to ensure that cats are given appropriate milk to maintain their health.</p>
</div>


