            <div style="flex: 3;">
                <h4 style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 8px;">Keep Your Cat at a Healthy Weight</h4>
                <p> A balanced diet is crucial for a cat's health and happiness. Kittens thrive on kitten-specific formulas, while adults need a diet that maintains a healthy weight. Veterinarians may recommend formulas with fewer calories for overweight cats. Feeding should be based on the bag's guidelines and monitored regularly. Cats are most likely to gain extra weight between 7 and 12. Cats should have multiple meals daily, with the size of meals reducing if overweight. Place small meals in different areas of the home to encourage natural hunting behavior. Exercise can help discourage destructive behavior and encourage independent play. If concerns about your cat's weight arise, consult your veterinarian for a plan to help them return to a healthy weight.</p>
            </div>

        </div>
